---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import { CoffeeCup, Gift, Mail, SendMail } from 'iconoir-react';
import yayImg from '../../assets/images/mailing-list-yay.png';
import Quote from '../shared/Quote.astro';
import LinkButton from '../shared/LinkButton.astro';
---

<div class='space-y-3 md:space-y-3'>
	<div class='space-y-3 md:space-y-3'>
		<h2
		transition:name="page-title"
			class='rounded-xl py-3 text-center font-serif text-lg font-bold xl:text-3xl'
		>
			<Mail className='inline text-2xl xl:text-4xl pr-4 text-amber-600' />
			The Occasional Email Experience
		</h2>

		<div class='relative top-3 clear-left flex flex-col md:flex-row'>
			<div class='flex flex-col items-center justify-center p-3'>
				<Image alt='hooray' src={yayImg} />
				<p class='mt-2 text-center text-xs italic'>
					the joy of receiving an email from Neil Hughes cannot be
					contained in a mere picture, but this comes close
				</p>
			</div>
			<div
				class='mb-6 mr-12 space-y-3 rounded bg-amber-100 px-12 py-6 md:space-y-6'
			>
				<p
					class='text-lg first-letter:float-left first-letter:pr-2 first-letter:text-5xl first-line:small-caps xl:text-2xl xl:first-letter:text-6xl'
				>
					Most emails are terrible. So I aim to make my emails a <strong
						class='text-red-500'>special occasion</strong
					>.
				</p>
				<p>
					<SendMail
						className='inline text-2xl xl:text-3xl pr-4 text-zinc-500'
					/> Sign up below and I&apos;ll send you <span
						class='font-bold text-green-600'
						>funny stories which may mildly improve your life</span
					>.
				</p>
				<p>
					<CoffeeCup
						className='inline text-2xl xl:text-3xl pr-4 text-zinc-500'
					/>
					When a rare email arrives, grab a cup of tea and settle in to
					enjoy.
				</p>
				<p class='leading-loose'>
					<Gift
						className='inline text-2xl xl:text-3xl pr-4 text-zinc-500'
					/>In your welcome email, I'll include the opening chapters
					of my books, <a
						href={`${
							import.meta.env.BASE_URL
						}books/walking-on-custard`}
						class='text-blue-500 underline hover:text-blue-400'
					>
						Walking on Custard
					</a>
					and
					<a
						href={`${
							import.meta.env.BASE_URL
						}books/shop-before-life`}
						class='text-blue-500 underline hover:text-blue-400'
						>The Shop Before Life</a
					>, for <strong class='text-red-500'>free</strong>.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class='mb-6 px-12'>
		<Quote
			quote={[
				'Your emails make me howl. With laughter, I hasten to add!',
				'I think they could be sold to a major publisher. Thank you for entertaining me.',
			]}
			cite={{ name: 'A long-time subscriber' }}
		/>
	</div>

	<div class="flex justify-center pt-6 pb-7 px-3 group">
		<LinkButton className='text-2xl font-serif pt-4 pb-5 px-5'  url='http://eepurl.com/gB3e8P' text="Click here to sign up!"/>
	</div>

	<div class='space-y-3 bg-violet-100 px-12 py-3 md:space-y-6'>
		<ul class='space-y-3 px-12'>
			<li>
				üëâ You can expect to receive an email newsletter from me
				‚Äòoccasionally‚Äô; in practice, this means roughly every few weeks
				to every few months.
			</li>
			<li>
				‚úçÔ∏è The content of these emails can be quite varied, but they
				tend to be mainly humorous or thought-provoking stories, along
				with roundups of links to interesting things I've found, and
				articles I've written recently.
			</li>
			<li>
				‚ùó I don't store any of your data myself: at the time of writing
				I am using <a
					href='http://mailchimp.com'
					class='text-blue-500 underline hover:text-blue-400'
				>
					Mailchimp</a
				> to manage my email list, which means they will store the data you
				provide on my behalf.
			</li>
			<li>
				ü•≥ Naturally, <strong>
					you can unsubscribe at any time</strong
				>‚Äîan unsubscribe link is provided in every email.
			</li>
		</ul>
	</div>
</div>
